---- MODULE YoYoNoPruning ----
plus  // TLA+ specification for Yo-YO leader election algorithm.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Nodes are represented by their integer identities, each node is executing in incoming/outgoing neighbors' mailboxes etc..
INVARIANT  AtLeastTwoSources {source} // Invariant to ensure that there will always be at least two source nodes.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Predicate asserting this as an invariant produces a state where all sources except for the leader are eliminated
LOCAL INSTANCE Phase {down, up} // Defining phase down or ‘up’ in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Note that each node retains "“Down” messages after executing a particular round because they are used during the Upphase
LOCAL INSTANCE Node {source, sink} // Defining source or sinks in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Predicate asserting that kind of node is determined ‘Source’ if it's a Source/Sink otherwise SINK
LOCAL INSTANCE Message {yes, no} // Defining message yes or No in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Messages sent during the algorithm are defined as ‘Yes’ if it's a 'No'-message otherwise
LOCAL INSTANCE Edge {reversed} // Defining edge reversal condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Edges along which the "no" message is sent during up phase change orientation of edges ‘yes’ if it's a 'No'-message otherwise
LOCAL INSTANCE Mailbox {empty, notEmpty} // Defining mail box condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Nodes are represented by their integer identities ‘mailBox’ is defined as empty or non-emtpy
LOCAL INSTANCE Round {one, two} // Defining round number condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Each node will have at most one source after a certain point ‘source’ is defined as only the leader or all nodes except for that
LOCAL INSTANCE State {stable, notStable} // Defining state condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    The algorithm stabilizes if there's at most one source node after a certain point ‘state’ is defined as stable or non-stabilized
LOCAL INSTANCE Leader {leader, notLead} // Defining leader condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    The algorithm ensures termination of the process by pruning graph ‘not’ defined as a node is identified with no incoming or outgoing neighbors
LOCAL INSTANCE Verification {valid, notValid} // Defining verification condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Formulas used for verifying the conditions are defined as valid/not-defined ‘verify’ is a function that takes two nodes (n & m) returns true iff n has received all values from neighbors of node 'm'
LOCAL INSTANCE Assertion {true, false} // Defining assertion condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Predicate asserting that there will always be at least two source nodes ‘assert’ is a function taking one node (n) returns true iff n has received all values from neighbors of any other neighbor
LOCAL INSTANCE Execution {executed, notExecut} // Defining execution condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Predicate asserting that there will always be at least two source nodes ‘execute’ is a function taking one node (n) returns true iff n has received all values from neighbors of any other neighbor
LOCAL INSTANCE Mailbox {empty, notEmpty} // Defining mail box condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Nodes are represented by their integer identities ‘mailBox’ is defined as empty or non-emtpy
LOCAL INSTANCE Round {one, two} // Defining round number condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Each node will have at most one source after a certain point ‘source’ is defined as only the leader or all nodes except for that
LOCAL INSTANCE State {stable, notStable} // Defining state condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    The algorithm stabilizes if there's at most one source node after a certain point ‘state’ is defined as stable or non-stabilized
LOCAL INSTANCE Leader {leader, notLead} // Defining leader condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    The algorithm ensures termination of the process by pruning graph ‘not’ defined as a node is identified with no incoming or outgoing neighbors
LOCAL INSTANCE Verification {valid, notValid} // Defining verification condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Formulas used for verifying the conditions are defined as valid/not-defined ‘verify’ is a function that takes two nodes (n & m) returns true iff n has received all values from neighbors of node 'm'
LOCAL INSTANCE Assertion {true, false} // Defining assertion condition in TLA+.   Author : Ludovic and Stephan Merz ,2019 .    Predicate asserting that there will always be at least two source nodes ‘assert’ is a function taking one node (n) returns true iff n has received all values from neighbors of any other neighbor
